10:32.527 --> 10:33.647
I'm dead.

10:38.867 --> 10:41.357
Listen. we're gonna have
to leave you guys here alone.

10:41.536 --> 10:44.896
Now. I know you're both mature.
responsible adults...

10:45.073 --> 10:48.513
...so try not to throw my toys
at each other. huh?

10:53.081 --> 10:54.981
Oh. great.

10:55.150 --> 10:57.680
One-thirty in the morning.

10:57.852 --> 11:00.292
Suppose you think
I'm any happier about that.

11:00.455 --> 11:04.385
You're a Russian. Karpov.
you're not allowed to be happy.

11:08.563 --> 11:10.863
Hi. it's me.

11:12.099 --> 11:16.559
Uh. it looks like I'm gonna be here
a little longer than I thought.

11:18.205 --> 11:19.925
How you feeling?

11:20.940 --> 11:24.040
What did the doctor
tell you about that?

11:24.210 --> 11:28.340
I know. Look. I'll be home
as soon as I can.

11:28.848 --> 11:30.868
Yeah. me too.

11:31.450 --> 11:33.180
Sweet dreams.

11:43.994 --> 11:46.934
Your wife. she's ill?

11:49.066 --> 11:50.966
Doctor told her to stay in bed.

11:51.135 --> 11:54.395
Oh. heh. She had to get up
and clean the house for a party.

11:55.806 --> 11:59.166
-Sounds like my wife.
-Oh?

11:59.343 --> 12:03.183
One time. she had pneumonia.
but that didn't stop her...

12:03.346 --> 12:07.676
...from walking our little Rosa 2 miles
to school through the freezing snow.

12:08.351 --> 12:11.691
-Heh. women.
-Yeah.

12:11.855 --> 12:15.345
You can't live with them.
and you can't live without them.

12:15.525 --> 12:17.885
I have been without for two months now.

12:19.896 --> 12:23.086
Even the dancing bear
started to look good.

